These routes must be created as static HTML pages or mapped through documented redirects before launch.

## Cloudflare Deployment Rules

Mandatory:

- static HTML
- semantic HTML
- minimal JavaScript
- Cloudflare Pages
- GitHub CI/CD

Forbidden:

- SPA routing
- runtime SEO
- client-side rendering for indexed content
- hydration SEO dependency

## Performance Targets

Hard limits:

- LCP under 1.8 seconds
- CLS under 0.05
- TTFB under 200 milliseconds
- minimized DOM depth
- no render-blocking JavaScript
- critical CSS inline where needed for launch performance

Cloudflare edge settings:

- HTTP/3
- Brotli
- Early Hints
- Tiered Cache
- Cache Everything
- Auto Minify
- Image Optimization
- Smart Compression

## UI System Rules

Master design principle:

The site must feel calm, executive, premium, spacious and low cognitive load.

Uniform spacing system:

Use an 8px base spacing system only.

Allowed scale:

- 8
- 16
- 24
- 32
- 48
- 64
- 96
- 128

No random spacing.

Every page must maintain:

- consistent vertical rhythm
- equalized card spacing
- uniform image ratios
- consistent CTA spacing
- aligned text widths
- consistent max-width containers

Required responsive breakpoints:

- 320
- 480
- 768
- 1024
- 1280
- 1440

Mobile UX rules:

- no text walls
- no oversized paragraphs
- no hidden semantic content
- no oversized hero sections
- no CLS image jumps

Typography rules:

- executive readability first
- short paragraphs
- 2 to 4 line maximum visible paragraph blocks where possible
- strong H2 hierarchy
- readable line-height
- high semantic chunking

